-- Mauritania Plans Quartz Mine, Awards Rights to Explore Titanium, Zirconium
-- B y   O u d a a   M a r o u f
-- 2010-10-15T06:37:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-15/mauritania-plans-quartz-mine-awards-rights-to-explore-titanium-zirconium.html
Mauritania awarded a mine license
for the establishment of a quartz operation to Mauritanian
Minerals Co. in the northern Oum Agneina area,  Mohamed Abdellahi Ould Oudaa , the country’s mines minister, said.  The mine, which will be 10 percent owned by the government,
will employ 300 people, Ould Oudaa told reporters in the
country’s capital, Nouakchott, yesterday.  The ministry also renewed a iron ore exploration license
held in the northern Tiferchai region by Wadi Al Rawda
Industrial Developments LLC and granted gold exploration
licenses to Alecto Holdings International in the central Wad
Amour area and to Massadir Sarl in the Bakel area.  A titanium and zirconium exploration license was awarded to
Mineralis Sarl in the northern El Abiod area, the minister said.  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
Oudaa Marouf in Nouakchott via Johannesburg at   asguazzin@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
